HEADWORD: Rhythmer
<hw>Rhyth"mer</hw> <pr>(r⟦icr⟧th"m⟦etil⟧r <it>or</it>
r⟦icr⟧⟦th⟧"-)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who writes in rhythm, esp. in
poetic rhythm or meter.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One now scarce counted a <qex>rhythmer</qex>, formerly admitted
